00:37:13.390 --> 00:37:15.740
Grassland management
ties into the vision

00:37:15.740 --> 00:37:17.450
of what we're talking
about on a larger

00:37:17.450 --> 00:37:21.300
scale, about 35,000
square miles.

00:37:21.300 --> 00:37:23.390
If you look to the
right, you will

00:37:23.390 --> 00:37:26.170
see grasslands that
have been overgrazed,

00:37:26.170 --> 00:37:29.050
which is why there are
no wildlife for quite

00:37:29.050 --> 00:37:30.710
awhile in North Kenya.

00:37:30.710 --> 00:37:33.190
Overgrazing or pastoral
communities-- we've got cows,

00:37:33.190 --> 00:37:35.360
we want them to have the grass.

00:37:35.360 --> 00:37:37.680
Tribal conflict-- you've
got better grass than I do.

00:37:37.680 --> 00:37:38.550
We're going at it.

00:37:38.550 --> 00:37:40.130
So that's what you
see on the right.

00:37:40.130 --> 00:37:43.120
What you see is through
the use of science

00:37:43.120 --> 00:37:45.590
and other things, the
redevelopment of grasslands,

00:37:45.590 --> 00:37:49.090
amazingly, cattle is the
way to redevelop grasslands.

00:37:49.090 --> 00:37:52.790
So by using cattle correctly
and by education and training,

00:37:52.790 --> 00:37:54.970
we can use cattle
to actually rebuild

00:37:54.970 --> 00:37:57.690
the grass, which makes the cows
fatter, which makes everybody

00:37:57.690 --> 00:37:59.439
happier, which takes
more money to market,

00:37:59.439 --> 00:38:01.200
which makes communities happier.

00:38:01.200 --> 00:38:04.760
So grassland management
is an incredible tool

00:38:04.760 --> 00:38:07.880
to help all these
pastoral communities.

00:38:07.880 --> 00:38:11.060
When the grasslands are
improved, wildlife comes back.

00:38:11.060 --> 00:38:13.450
Because wildlife knows
where the good grasses are.

00:38:13.450 --> 00:38:15.360
So now we have to
work on how do we

00:38:15.360 --> 00:38:19.360
mitigate the challenges between
the grassland and the wildlife

00:38:19.360 --> 00:38:20.945
for cattle and so forth.

00:38:20.945 --> 00:38:22.320
There's been a
lot of great stuff

00:38:22.320 --> 00:38:25.480
that we're working on with
lion predation and so forth

00:38:25.480 --> 00:38:28.770
to actually educate how to
protect cattle from wildlife.

00:38:28.770 --> 00:38:31.716
These are low technology
things that we've been doing,

00:38:31.716 --> 00:38:33.090
and they've been
very successful.

00:38:33.090 --> 00:38:35.270
But now we're looking at
it on a much bigger scale,

00:38:35.270 --> 00:38:37.390
so we have to start getting
a lot more creative in how

